# Update User Guide

When you make **user-facing changes** to ZSMS, update `docs/USER_GUIDE.md` in the **same session** before finishing. Bump the **Last updated** date (YYYY-MM-DD) at the top of that file.

## When to update (required)

| Change type | Update these sections |
| ----------- | --------------------- |
| New/removed dashboard page or sidebar item | Role navigation tables for affected role(s); sync from `components/dashboard/Sidebar.js` |
| New/removed platform admin page | Platform admin navigation table; sync from `components/platform/PlatformShell.js` |
| New user workflow (onboarding, ECZ, timetable, attendance, billing, SMS, mobile) | Cross-role workflows + affected role's "Key workflows" |
| New/changed subscription plan or pricing | Subscription and billing, Feature availability by plan |
| New portal type or role | Executive summary, Getting started, new role section |
| Login, password, or access flow change | Getting started |
| Mobile app feature added/removed | Mobile app section; note web-only vs mobile scope |
| Solo/individual portal change | Solo teacher portal section |
| Troubleshooting for new common issue | Troubleshooting table |

## When to skip

- Backend-only refactors with no UI or workflow change
- Developer-only API changes not exposed in dashboards
- Typo fixes, styling-only edits, or copy tweaks that do not change behaviour
- Test-only changes

## How to update

1. Read the current `docs/USER_GUIDE.md`.
2. Verify routes against `Sidebar.js`, `PlatformShell.js`, and actual `app/dashboard/` pages.
3. Edit only sections affected by your change; link to deeper docs (ECZ, SMS, offline) rather than duplicating them.
4. Set **Last updated** to today's date.

If unsure whether a change is user-facing, update the doc — prefer accuracy over omission.

Also update `docs/SYSTEM_DOCUMENTATION.md` when the change affects architecture, APIs, schema, or integrations (see `.cursor/rules/update-system-documentation.mdc`).
